#TrackNigeria The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has cleared a governorship aspirant, Babatunde Ayo Kunle Irukera to contest the party’s Kogi governorship primaries. A statement by the National Publicity Secretary of the party, Mr Issa Lanre-Onilu Wednesday said Irukera successfully met the conditions provided by the party’s guidelines for the nomination of candidates within the time granted to clarify his claims.